# Validation commands

When running project validation, use documented `make` targets instead of calling tools directly.

- Prefer `make test` for the full suite (`pytest test/unit test/integration`), or `make unit` / `make integration` when you need that scope.
- Prefer `make lint` / `make lint-fix` for formatting and linting.
- Do not run `pytest`, `ruff`, or other validation tools directly unless the user explicitly asks for that command.
